summary: This FBI 302 form documents a meeting on December 18, 2020, where a Palm Beach County Sheriff's Office detective served an individual with a federal grand jury subpoena from the Southern District of New York. The individual acknowledged knowing the topic of the investigation and agreed to cooperate and speak with agents in New York.

persons.name: Detective
persons.role: Palm Beach County Sheriff's Office Detective
persons.context: Participated in the investigation and the meeting where the subpoena was served.

persons.name: NYPD Detective IIII
persons.context: Was to contact the subpoenaed individual by phone on the evening of December 18, 2020.

connections.description: Collaborated in the investigation and the service of a grand jury subpoena.
SA informed the subject that NYPD Detective IIII would make contact as part of the coordinated investigation.

events.title: Service of Grand Jury Subpoena
events.description: A Palm Beach County Sheriff's Office detective and an FBI SA served a federal grand jury subpoena to an individual in Boynton Beach, Florida. The individual acknowledged knowing the topic and agreed to cooperate.

events.title: Scheduled Grand Jury Appearance
events.description: The subpoena commanded the individual to appear at the U.S. Courthouse at 40 Foley Square in New York City.

locations: 40 Foley Square, Room 220, New York City, New York
keyFacts: A federal grand jury subpoena was served on December 18, 2020, in Boynton Beach, Florida, as part of the SDNY investigation.
The individual served stated they 'knew what they wanted to talk to him about' and agreed to cooperate with the investigation.
The subpoena commanded the individual to appear in New York City on January 14, 2021.
The document is an FBI 302 form, indicating it is an official report of an investigative activity.
The document is subject to a protective order, restricting its distribution.
